SENATE RESOLUTION 355
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to honor Impact Baptist Church and Ministries in
Memphis on the occasion of its twentieth
anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should recognize those venerable religious
institutions and their ministers and congregations that, through their unflagging capacity for love,
dedication of spirit, and faith in God, enrich the lives of people in their communities; and
WHEREAS, one such dynamic and historic community of faith is Impact Baptist Church
and Ministries in Memphis, led by Dr. Michael C. Ellis, Sr., whose members are commemorating
the church's twentieth anniversary this year with a joyous celebration on April 26, 2026; and
WHEREAS, Impact Baptist Church and Ministries traces its roots to 2006, when Pastor
Ellis established the ministry, which has stood on the rock-solid foundation of Christian belief,
service, and love for twenty years, serving as a bastion of faith and outreach to the people of its
community; and
WHEREAS, Impact Baptist Church and Ministries offers a number of programs and
ministries, including preschool, missions, military, youth, singles, and recreation ministries in
addition to their Legions Ministry, which serves senior adults aged fifty-five and older; and
WHEREAS, an inspirational leader of his congregation, Pastor Ellis is a graduate of
Union Theological Seminary, Golden Grain Bible College and Seminary, and Jacksonville
Theological Seminary; and
WHEREAS, Impact Baptist Church and Ministries is truly one of the great religious
institutions and catalysts for positive spiritual change in our State and nation, and the members
of this exceptional congregation should be appropriately honored for their exemplary service to
their fellow Christians and to the good people of Tennessee; now, therefore,
SR0355
015721
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we join in the celebration of the
twentieth anniversary of Impact Baptist Church and Ministries, thank the members of this
historic congregation and its pastor, Dr. Michael C. Ellis, Sr., for their notable service to their
Lord and the State of Tennessee, and wish them much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
